 Fort Beaufort - The Raymond Mhlaba Local Municipality says it has been granted a court interdict against Eskom by the Grahamstown High Court. "The court interdict is preventing the Power Utility from continuing with its planned bulk electricity supply disruptions in Adelaide, Bedford, and Fort Beaufort from the 23 December 2019," said Raymond Mhlaba Municipality Communications Manager, Sivenkosi Mtiya. "Through its Lawyers, Raymond Mhlaba Municipality will continue to engage Eskom until an amicable solution is reached. "Furthermore, the Municipality apologises for the inconvenience caused as a result of the statement sent by Eskom and wants to assure all of its residents, businesses and stakeholders that it's still committed to deliver uninterrupted services." The municipality had said that it only learnt of Eskom's planned power cuts through the media. It had promised it would do everything possible to keep the lights. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  